'''Zawyet el-Maiyitin''' or '''Zawyet Sultan''' or '''Zawyet el-Amwat''' is a small village in [[Egypt]], located in the [[Minya Governorate]].
The site has a small step-[[pyramid]] of the late [[Third dynasty of Egypt|3rd Dynasty]], remarkable for being the only pyramid built on the east bank of the [[Nile]]. It also comprises [[rock-cut tomb]]s of the late [[Old Kingdom of Egypt|Old Kingdom]].
==External links== {{commons category}} * [http://www.egyptsites.co.uk/middle/minya/maiyitin.html EgyptSites article]
