{{coord|30|47|40|N|30|36|01|E|type:landmark|display=title}}

'''Anthylla''' is an ancient city of [[Lower Egypt]], on the [[Canopus]] branch of the [[Nile river]]. [[Herodotus]] and [[Athenaeus]] report that it provided furnishings for the queen of Egypt. It is sometimes thought to be the ancient city of [[Gynaecopolis]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/text?doc=Perseus:text:1999.04.0064:entry=anthylla-geo|title=Dictionary of Greek and Roman Geography |publisher=Perseus.tufts.edu |date= |accessdate=2012-11-10}}</ref>

